## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I am genuinely working through: how do smaller healthcare organizations — clinics, community health centers, organizations running OpenMRS in low-resource settings — realistically meet compliance requirements when they have limited staff and budget?

HIPAA applies to them the same as it applies to a large hospital system, but the resources are not comparable. I do not think the answer is "just do your best and hope for the most" — but I also do not have a clear picture yet of what realistic compliance looks like at that scale. This feels like an important question for the kind of environments OpenMRS is actually deployed in, and I want to think about it more as the project progresses.

